    <h1>Why water is important to life.</h1>
    <p>Water makes up about <b>75%</b> of the body composition, <br /> therefore this shows that we as humans can't do without it.</p>
    <hr />
    <h2>Composition of water.</h2>
    <p>Water is made up of 2 parts of <b>Hydrogen</b>(H<sub>2</sub>) and 1 part of <b>Oxygen</b>(O) <br />  i.e H<sub>2</sub>+ O = H<sub>2</sub>O.</p>
    <h3>Forms of water.</h3>
    <p><ol>
        <li>Blood</li>
        <li>Ice</li>
        <li>Snow</li>
    </ol></p>
    <p><dl>
        <dt>Blood</dt>
        <dd>contains plasma and water found in the human body.</dd>
        <dt>Ice</dt>
        <dd>water that has been frozen for a while.</dd>
        <dt>Snow</dt>
        <dd>Water falls in a solidified form in certain regions during winter.</dd>
    </dl></p>
    <p>Earth has the                   most amount of water surrounding it</p>
